      <h2>Our Story</h2>
      <p>In 2018, we began as a small group on the Belvedere Estate. The pandemic changed everything—not just how we worked, but who we served. Recognizing that everyone in our community needed a place to reconnect, we transitioned into Community Men in Sheds Taunton (CMIST).</p>
      <p>A whirlwind 2021 saw us move to a much larger facility and achieve official Charity status. Today, our new home near Taunton Station allows us to host double the members across two floors of specialized workshops and outdoor space. Whether you’re here to wood-work, socialize, or learn a new skill, there’s a place for you at the Shed.</p>



      <h2>Join us!</h2>
      <p>All are welcome whatever their age, gender or background. Annual membership is £20 per person, plus £3 per session.</p>
      <p>CMIST currently meets from
      10:30am - 3:30pm:
      Tuesdays 
      Wednesday </p>


